import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['speed'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Wind Speed (m/s)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wind speed across all locations?')
    
    ax = plt.gca()
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['dir'], data['speed'])
    plt.xlabel('Wind Direction (degrees)')
    plt.ylabel('Wind Speed (m/s)')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title('What is the relationship between wind direction and wind speed?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    dirCat_counts = data['dirCat'].value_counts()
    dirCat_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.xlabel('Categorized Wind Direction')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of categorized wind direction across all locations?')

    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;
